cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes an unsupervised method for sentence summarization using language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses two language models, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and ranking, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves neural networks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
